    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a5e23138_a2e5fd5f",
        "filename": "org.eclipse.jgit/src/org/eclipse/jgit/signing/GpgProcessConfiguration.java",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 17,
      "author": {
        "id": 1021966
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-28T20:51:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This strikes me as overkill. First, it could be a record. But in effect only (false, false) or (true, true) make sense. So why not simply pass a single boolean instead of this configuration object?\n\nAlso, the process runner parses both stdout and stderr to implement rejectTerminalPrompt. Why not tell it which stream to parse?\n\nWith that you end up with three boolean flags in the GpgProcessRunner constructor (calledFromGui, failOnNonZero, gpgStatusOnStderr), which is a bit ugly. Maybe use an enum and a Set\u003cenum\u003e?\n```\nenum GpgProcessExecutionSetting {\n  FORBID_TERMINAL_PROMPT, FAIL_ON_NON_ZERO, GPG_STATUS_ON_STDERR\n}\n\n// Constructor\nGpgProcessRunner(..., Set\u003cGpgProcessExecutionSetting\u003e settings) { ... }\n```\nAs it\u0027s all internal, not public API, even using three int constants (1, 2, 4) and simply or-ing them would be OK I think.",
      "revId": "ced3f77ccfae96c05308c67eb0647e5aa0683c9d",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
